==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hindsight
<hw>hindsight</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>understanding the nature of an
event after it has happened; <as>as, <ex>hindsight</ex> is always
clearer than foresight</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>20-20 hindsight</b></col>, <col><b>twenty-twenty
hindsight</b></col></mcol> <cd>Perfect understanding of an event after
it has happened; -- a term usually used with sarcasm in response to
criticism of one's decision, implying that the critic is unfairly
judging the wisdom of the decision in light of information that was not
available when the decision was made.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hindu</ent>⟦br⟧
